### IaC State / Concurrency (Terraform) — Pro SRE Hands-On

State & Locks
- terraform state list                      # Inspect what’s tracked
- terraform plan                            # See drift/errors
- Check DynamoDB lock table (S3 backend)    # Look for stale locks

Unlocking (Caution)
- terraform force-unlock <LOCK_ID>          # Only if you’ve verified no active run
- Prefer to cancel/complete the stuck run from CI before force-unlocking

Backend Sanity (S3/GCS/Blob)
- Ensure bucket + lock table permissions (s3:Get/Put/Delete; DDB Get/Put/Update)
- Re-init if backend misconfigured:
  terraform init -backend-config=backend.hcl

CI/CD Safety
- Serialize applies per env with concurrency groups.
- Add policy checks (OPA/Conftest/Kyverno) for resources, probes, and secrets.
